Dialogue: 0,0:01:31.80,0:01:34.36,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Ladies and gentlemen,\ngood evening.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:34.97,0:01:37.10,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Anguish. Anxiety.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:37.67,0:01:40.30,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Because his soul is so\npure and innocent,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:40.41,0:01:43.21,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,...it is all the more susceptible to\nbecoming troubled and tarnished.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:43.81,0:01:48.41,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,The tarnish becomes an indelible stain,\nand the stain gradually spreads.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:49.39,0:01:53.08,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,When one is no longer\nable to trust others,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:53.56,0:01:57.43,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,...is that when one truly\nbecomes an adult?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:01.01,0:02:04.01,count fo,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,{\pos(352,350)}Act 15:\NThe End of Happiness, The Beginning of Truth
Dialogue: 0,0:02:23.82,0:02:27.38,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,It's amazing how tiny and insignificant\nthe world we live on is.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:27.56,0:02:32.33,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Yes. In the vast cosmos,\nit is but a grain of sand.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:32.56,0:02:36.90,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,And what's more, separated from Earth by\na distance of 2:5 light years as we now are,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:37.27,0:02:42.90,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,...the light you are now seeing\nis that of 25 years ago.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:44.27,0:02:45.97,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,25 years?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:47.14,0:02:49.48,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Indeed. 25 years.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:52.25,0:02:55.05,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,I'm glad that you brought me\nwith you.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:55.62,0:03:01.72,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Seen from space, all the things that I was\nagonizing over seem so insignificant.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:02.09,0:03:08.73,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Perhaps, but hatred and malice are\namplified in the darkness of space.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:25.82,0:03:30.75,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Everyone's gone away...\NFranz has left, and so has Albert.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:32.86,0:03:35.62,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,I'm sorry for asking you to meet me\non such short notice, Franz.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:35.83,0:03:37.82,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,That's all right,\NI'm glad I had the chance to see you.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:37.93,0:03:40.19,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,I'm planning on setting out\non a trip for a while.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:42.17,0:03:43.72,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Is Albert going\nwith you?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:44.13,0:03:47.07,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Apparently, he went off somewhere\non a trip of his own.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:47.40,0:03:49.84,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Even though his father's in the\nmiddle of an election campaign.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:50.17,0:03:51.33,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Can you believe\nthat guy?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:51.68,0:03:52.84,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,"Somewhere"?\NWhere do you mean?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:53.31,0:03:56.30,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,I'm sorry,\NI don't know, either.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:57.25,0:03:58.04,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Oh.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:58.15,0:04:00.31,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,The one thing I can\nsay for sure...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:00.65,0:04:03.85,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,...is that he's gotten himself mixed\nup in something dangerous.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:04.02,0:04:06.15,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,He still hasn't figured\nthat out, though.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:07.76,0:04:09.49,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Franz, I...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:09.69,0:04:12.25,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,I know.\NYou're a victim in all this, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:13.23,0:04:17.29,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Listen, whatever happens,\ndon't forget who you are.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:17.97,0:04:20.44,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Look for the truth\non your own.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:39.16,0:04:41.28,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Before I made\nyour acquaintance,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:41.39,0:04:46.29,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,...I traveled to the far reaches of the universe,\noperating this ship by myself.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:46.83,0:04:48.76,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,You flew a huge ship like this\nby yourself?!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:49.40,0:04:56.03,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Yes. At the time, I was quite proud of the fact\nthat I was able to operate it single-handedly.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:56.67,0:04:59.11,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Come, take a look\nat that.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:59.61,0:05:00.51,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,What is that?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:00.94,0:05:04.90,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,The Milky Way. I am told that in the ancient\NOrient, it was called the River of Heaven.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:05.28,0:05:06.51,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,The River of Heaven?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:07.25,0:05:09.52,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,This is what I wished\nto show to you.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:10.65,0:05:12.52,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,It's so beautiful...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:12.66,0:05:16.46,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,According to their legends, two lovers\nlived on the opposite banks...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:16.56,0:05:20.19,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,...separated from one another\nby the River of Heaven.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:20.63,0:05:24.90,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,They say that once a year, they cross\nthe river and are reunited.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:24.97,0:05:26.87,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,That's a romantic story,\ndon't you think?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:29.01,0:05:33.31,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Long ago, I once had a friend,\na sailor who was born in Marseilles.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:33.64,0:05:37.08,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,I heard that story\nmany times from him.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:38.58,0:05:41.55,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,I bet that your friend\nwas in love.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:43.55,0:05:49.65,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,This sailor of whom I speak had a beautiful\nfiancée and a best friend he felt at ease around.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:50.39,0:05:55.35,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,These three were childhood friends,\nand were always looking out for each other.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:55.90,0:06:01.13,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Indeed, they were much like you,\NMonsieur Franz, and Mademoiselle Eugenie.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:02.51,0:06:08.31,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,However, the best friend was secretly\nin love with the sailor's fiancée.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:08.91,0:06:14.87,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,And then, the friend, who would stop\nat nothing to possess the fiancée,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:15.22,0:06:19.99,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,...framed the sailor for a crime\nwhich he did not commit.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:21.16,0:06:24.75,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Unbeknownst to anyone, the poor sailor\nspent more than a dozen years...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:25.10,0:06:28.55,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,...chained up in a prison located\nin the depths of space.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:36.57,0:06:38.01,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,I can't believe it...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:38.34,0:06:40.14,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,However, a miraculous\nevent occurred,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:40.38,0:06:43.74,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,...and the sailor was set free, whereupon\nhe returned to Marseilles.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:44.28,0:06:45.98,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,I'm relieved\nto hear that.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:46.08,0:06:51.89,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,However, the beautiful fiancée, rather\nthan waiting for the sailor's return,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:52.22,0:06:54.28,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,...had become engaged\nto his friend instead.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:57.43,0:06:58.89,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,That's terrible...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:59.86,0:07:03.26,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,I wonder why she didn't wait\nfor the sailor to come home?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:03.77,0:07:08.73,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Also, why did the sailor's friend steal away\nhis fiancée in spite of their friendship?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:09.24,0:07:15.91,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,The sailor, now betrayed by both his best friend\nand his fiancée, never returned to Earth again.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:20.45,0:07:22.51,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Why do you cry?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:23.05,0:07:24.42,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,I don't know...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:25.12,0:07:31.25,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Until just recently, I thought that I would\nnever believe in anyone, just as you do.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:31.96,0:07:33.95,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,That's what I told myself...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:34.56,0:07:37.36,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,But for some reason,\nwhen I see your face,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:37.63,0:07:42.40,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,...that thought of living that way seems\nlike the saddest thing in the world to me.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:47.34,0:07:52.11,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Count, let's have faith that our friendship\nwill be the exception to the rule!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:52.68,0:07:55.62,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,At the very least, you're the one person\nthat I can trust!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:58.72,0:08:03.13,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Is the watch that I gave you\nstill ticking away?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:08.93,0:08:14.70,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Albert, I shall be departing Paris\nsometime in the near future.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:16.44,0:08:18.14,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,What do you mean,\NCount?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:18.74,0:08:20.21,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,It's so sudden!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:20.64,0:08:22.84,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Wait, it's not because of\nyour illness, is it?!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:23.21,0:08:28.01,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,No. There was a certain matter\nthat I had to see to in Paris,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:28.25,0:08:31.58,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,...which is why I have kept my residence\non the Champs Elysees.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:32.19,0:08:37.99,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,However, the task I came to accomplish\nwill soon be completed.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:38.30,0:08:45.70,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Morcerf! Morcerf!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:56.65,0:08:59.95,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Don't say such things!\NPlease, stay in Paris for good!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:00.05,0:09:05.04,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Or if that's not possible, please take me\nwith you when you go!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:05.69,0:09:08.09,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,I don't want to\nbe apart from you!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:09.86,0:09:13.52,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Do you think that\nhighly of me?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:13.76,0:09:14.86,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,I do!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:17.63,0:09:20.50,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,The ardor of youth\neventually cools.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:20.60,0:09:25.41,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,That's not true!\NYou... To me, you're...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:28.28,0:09:29.40,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,One day...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:30.61,0:09:34.28,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,One day, I will ask you\nthe same question.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:34.75,0:09:39.42,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,I wonder if you will still feel\nthe same way about me then?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:44.29,0:09:46.49,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Excellency, there's a message\nfrom Paris.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:48.23,0:09:49.99,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,If you will pardon me\nfor a moment...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:07.55,0:10:10.25,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Monsieur Noirtier...\NPlease, you have to tell me.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:10.79,0:10:12.98,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Tell me what\NGankutsuou is.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:39.65,0:10:41.98,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,What's this?\NHey, wait a minute!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:53.56,0:10:58.63,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,"In the event of an emergency, it is possible\nfor a third party who knows the password..."
Dialogue: 0,0:10:59.04,0:11:01.97,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,"...to use this pen to make contact\nwith its owner."
Dialogue: 0,0:11:02.44,0:11:07.14,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Does this mean that if I can figure out the\npassword, I can access your mind directly?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:19.89,0:11:21.55,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,She's so beautiful!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:21.66,0:11:22.75,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, isn't she...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:22.86,0:11:24.83,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Right. She's Monte Cristo's...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:31.07,0:11:35.60,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,I realize I am late, but I have come to offer\nmy support to you, General Morcerf.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:35.91,0:11:37.40,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Well, well!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:37.51,0:11:39.94,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,By all means, please\nstep up to the podium!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:53.42,0:11:59.46,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Valentine... I'm certain that your grandfather\ntold you a very important password.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:00.23,0:12:01.46,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Do you know\nwhat it is?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:05.67,0:12:10.07,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Valentine, I am now surrounded\non all sides by enemies.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:10.61,0:12:16.44,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,If anything should happen to my body,\nremember this flower.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:20.28,0:12:21.94,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Blue rose...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:31.09,0:12:32.96,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,My name is Haidee.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:33.06,0:12:35.22,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Various circumstances\nbrought me to Paris,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:35.33,0:12:39.70,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,...and I have eagerly awaited the day that\NI would be able to meet General Morcerf.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:40.00,0:12:42.23,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Goodness, you honor me.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:42.77,0:12:46.54,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,This may sound rude, but have we met\nsomewhere before, by any chance?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:46.98,0:12:50.07,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, ten years ago.\NI will never forget the day.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:50.38,0:12:53.37,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,When I was four years old,\nin the land of Janina.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:53.58,0:12:54.57,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Janina?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:54.88,0:13:00.05,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,You did us the honor of protecting us\nas a gallant Space Forces officer.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:00.56,0:13:02.39,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, is that it?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:03.26,0:13:05.99,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,You were a patriot dedicated\nto defending our country.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:06.10,0:13:09.76,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Or so I believed,\nuntil that day.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:15.00,0:13:16.06,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Done!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:35.66,0:13:39.46,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,I never expected that I would be using\nthis channel for this purpose...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:39.86,0:13:44.10,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Still, I have no further need for it\nnow that I have left politics behind.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:45.07,0:13:46.73,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Thank you, Franz.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:47.57,0:13:50.63,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,You and your friends have kept\nmy granddaughter safe for me.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:51.27,0:13:54.84,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,If there is anything in my memories that might\nprove useful to you, by all means, take them.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:55.75,0:13:59.77,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Please take good care\nof Valentine.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:04.19,0:14:06.38,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,W-Who in the world\nare you?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:06.99,0:14:11.76,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,I am a sad woman who had the misfortune\nto lose her father at Janina,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:12.20,0:14:17.26,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,...and to be handed over to slave\ntraders along with her mother.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:21.91,0:14:27.24,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,My father fell victim to the intrigues of a certain\nyoung officer, and lost his life as a result.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:27.38,0:14:28.57,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, my!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:29.31,0:14:30.94,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,What's she talking about?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:32.58,0:14:36.58,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,I-I'm curious as to what this story\nhas to do with these proceedings?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:36.75,0:14:41.09,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,They have no bearing on this? Is that what\nyou are trying to say, General Morcerf?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:41.46,0:14:43.98,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Or Fernand Mondego,\nshould I say?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:44.43,0:14:45.53,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:45.21,0:14:46.48,count alt,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,What does she mean?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:46.35,0:14:48.18,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Who IS that woman?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:47.64,0:14:48.66,count alt,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,"Mondego"?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:52.67,0:14:54.69,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Gankutsuou is...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:01.48,0:15:03.57,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,The Chateau d'lf.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:14.36,0:15:16.33,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Edmond Dantes.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:19.83,0:15:21.85,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,My name is\NHaidee Tebelin,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:22.50,0:15:28.03,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,...daughter of Ali Tebelin, former Pasha\nof Janina, and his wife, Vasiliki!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:30.97,0:15:34.64,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,I am the daughter of a father who\nwas brought low by your conspiracy...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:34.74,0:15:38.04,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,...and a mother who lost\nher life to despair!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:41.38,0:15:44.05,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Surely you can offer no justification\nfor what you did.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:44.59,0:15:46.52,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,W-What's this nonsense?!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:46.62,0:15:48.82,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Ladies and gentlemen,\nit is THIS that is a conspiracy!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:49.16,0:15:52.65,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,A rebellion by malcontents who\nare trying to disrupt my campaign!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:52.76,0:15:54.96,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,He's right! Grab that woman\nand get her out of here!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:55.06,0:15:56.79,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,It's a conspiracy!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:56.16,0:15:57.69,count alt,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Don't fall for her lies, everyone!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:58.77,0:16:01.26,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Now, I think you\nshould leave.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:01.37,0:16:03.70,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Shut your mouth,\NFernand Mondego!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:10.25,0:16:13.51,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,What's this?\NDon't look at me like that!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:14.62,0:16:16.71,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Are you able to prove\nwhat you say?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:27.26,0:16:29.09,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Why, that's...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:29.47,0:16:34.10,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Proof that will never fade for as long as I live.\NProof that was branded onto me...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:34.17,0:16:36.20,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,...when I was turned over to\nthe slave traders by that man.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:37.01,0:16:40.31,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,This brand is a record of everything\nthat I have endured.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:43.35,0:16:47.54,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Haidee... This belonged to your father.\NTake it.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:47.82,0:16:52.62,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,If you ever suspect that you are about to\nbe violated, use this to take your own life.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:00.70,0:17:04.60,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Fernand Mondego. Change your name\nall you like,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:05.37,0:17:08.74,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,...but the blood of my father that splattered\nonto your forehead that day...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:09.24,0:17:11.10,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,...will never disappear as\nlong as you shall live!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:36.07,0:17:40.66,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Ali... I... I know\NI'm right.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:41.10,0:17:42.59,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,I did the right thing.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:43.17,0:17:46.97,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,He is my sworn enemy, the man\nwho stole everything from me.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:47.71,0:17:49.68,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,So why do I feel\nlike this?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:55.25,0:17:56.45,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Ali...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:59.69,0:18:06.49,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,The Count... I must warn him!\NI mustn't let the Count suffer as I do now!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:16.47,0:18:19.50,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Count... Has something happened?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:20.04,0:18:22.24,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Why do you seem\nso anxious?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:22.55,0:18:23.91,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,I'm not sure.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:24.21,0:18:28.34,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,I just sense the presence of\na deep, terrible darkness.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:29.39,0:18:32.15,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Count, what should I...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:32.26,0:18:36.16,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Albert, you should return to Earth.\NWithout delay.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:37.83,0:18:40.66,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,You should be at your\nfather's side.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:41.16,0:18:42.29,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,My father?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:43.23,0:18:47.00,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,It's times like these when a man makes a lot\nof enemies. You should watch your back, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:47.40,0:18:49.77,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Has something happened\nto my father?!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:49.97,0:18:54.34,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Return home at once. I will lend you\nmy ship, the Spada.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:58.41,0:19:01.87,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,The time has come at last\nfor you to learn everything.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:04.62,0:19:07.45,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,This may be the last time\nwe meet.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:07.59,0:19:08.39,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,No!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:09.76,0:19:14.09,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Fare thee well,\NAlbert my friend.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:16.83,0:19:17.99,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Count...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:22.87,0:19:27.61,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Why? I thought we were going\nto trust only each other...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:28.38,0:19:29.61,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Count!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:31.35,0:19:32.34,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Count!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:48.33,0:19:49.32,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Count!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:52.80,0:19:53.73,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Count!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:56.11,0:19:57.23,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Count!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:58.61,0:20:00.24,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Count!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:15.15,0:21:16.14,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,We're going back!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:16.25,0:21:19.42,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Back to that city where\nvice flourishes!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:23.56,0:21:26.53,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Stand by for\natmospheric reentry.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:10.90,0:23:12.27,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Everything was\na lie.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:12.74,0:23:15.17,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,The tiny rip becomes\nan enormous tear,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:15.34,0:23:17.77,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,...and everything I had believed in\nfalls in and is swallowed up by it.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:18.31,0:23:20.94,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Next time on Gankutsuou,\NThe Count of Monte Cristo act 16:
Dialogue: 0,0:23:19.87,0:23:21.38,count fo,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,{\pos(352,350)}Act 16:\NScandal
Dialogue: 0,0:23:20.94,0:23:21.87,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,..."Scandal."
Dialogue: 0,0:23:22.21,0:23:24.87,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Bide your time,\nand hold out hope!
